@node Main "Multi_Q - Documentation"

                             'Multi_Q' 1.12

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Multi_Q' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} that includes 3 of my previous
Q-games, all in one program. The game boards included are: Tri_Q,
Hexa_Q, X_Q ...and an additional (bonus) board.

  You play by jumping a peg to an empty space either horizontally
or diagonally, and depending if you play the @{" Normal " link play} or @{" Inverted " link play}
game, that peg must go over another peg (or empty space in the
Inverted game). In the @{" Normal " link play} game, the intermediate peg (the one
that was jumped over) will be removed. In the @{" Inverted " link play} game, the
intermediate empty space will be replaced by a peg.

  The goal is to remove all the pegs, leaving only one on the board.
If you play the @{" Inverted " link play} game, you start with one peg and you try
to fill the board leaving only one empty space.

  Have fun!

